# Arc E2E testing (Cursor)

Copy this file to `.cursor/rules/e2e-testing.mdc` (`.cursor/` is gitignored).

## When this applies

- Changing storefront UI, Weave sections, WP plugin REST/editor, cart/checkout, or cache/webhooks
- User asks to verify, test, or ship a UI feature

## Required reading

- `Documentation/Testing/TESTING.md`
- `Documentation/Testing/UX-RULES.md`
- `Design-Systems/Arc-Design/SKILL.md` before CSS/JSX changes

## Before marking UI work complete

1. Run `pnpm test` and `pnpm test:contract` if touching `@arc/*` or `@weave/*`
2. Run `pnpm test:e2e:smoke` if touching user-visible flows
3. If E2E failed: read `Artifacts/e2e-reports/latest.json` and fix **all P0/P1 tickets** before claiming done

## Writing tests

- **Per-app** Playwright projects only — no monolithic root suite
- Tag: `@smoke` for PR gate; `@quarantine` only with linked issue
- Assert Arc design tokens and COMMERCE.md UX states (see UX-RULES.md)
- Visual regression required for layout changes (`toHaveScreenshot`)
- Use `@axe-core/playwright` on every route in smoke set

## Agent fixes from failures

Implement `tickets[].suggestedFix` in order: P0 → P1 → P2. Cite `requirementIds` in commit messages.

Do not weaken assertions to green tests without product approval.
